                        <p>UCF’s Professional Master of Science in Management (PMSM), with a concentration in Human Resources, is a unique 16-month evening program. It enables working professionals who aspire to take on leadership roles in human resource or general management to earn an accredited Master’s degree in an accelerated timeframe.</p>
<p>Classes begin in Downtown Orlando in January 2014</p>

<h3>Curriculum</h3>

<p>PMSM classes meet Tuesday & Thursday evenings, 6:00-9:50 p.m., at the Executive Development Center’s state-of-the-art downtown facility.</p>
<p>The 30-credit hour curriculum comprises five sessions over 16 months with courses covering general management and business strategy as well as advanced offerings in HR management. Participants gain the latest business techniques and knowledge for success in today’s competitive marketplace.</p>
<p>View a list of courses currently taught in the PMSM.</p>

